# Code owners for the @clerk/javascript release and CI control plane.
#
# These paths are the supply-chain surface: workflows, composite actions, the
# package manager + workspace config, the release/changeset config, and the
# dependency-intake config. A change here can reach OIDC publishing, alter what
# gets packed into published tarballs, or weaken the workflow trust boundary, so
# every change requires review from the team that owns the release pipeline.
#
# Routing alone does not enforce review: it is only enforced once branch
# protection requires Code Owner approval on these paths (the admin half of
# SDK-79). See SDK-79 / Monorepo Supply-Chain Hardening.

# Entire GitHub Actions surface: workflows and composite actions.
/.github/                                 @clerk/sdk-infra

# Package manager, workspace, and root manifest.
/.npmrc                                   @clerk/sdk-infra
/pnpm-workspace.yaml                      @clerk/sdk-infra
/package.json                             @clerk/sdk-infra

# Build, release, and changeset config.
/turbo.json                               @clerk/sdk-infra
/.changeset/config.json                   @clerk/sdk-infra

# Dependency intake.
/renovate.json5                           @clerk/sdk-infra
/scripts/renovate-config-generator.mjs    @clerk/sdk-infra

# Supply-chain guard scripts (must not be neutered without review).
/scripts/check-workflow-triggers.mjs      @clerk/sdk-infra
